title: [Whistler's Pass, Tunnel]
description: A massive, wooden arch has been erected in the tunnel here, its limbs and supports covering a ten-foot span of the irregular ceiling.  Formed from stout felwood timber and banded with thick mithril straps, the arch appears to be quite sturdy.  Minute, vein-like cracks in the stone ceiling and walls may have initiated the need for its construction in this area.
